2025-05-27 02:53:18,421 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=CategoryTitle, text='Answers' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,422 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 1. Before becoming a U.S. Senator, what position did Tammy Baldwin hold? → Member of the House of Representatives' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,422 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 2. What is 'freedom of speech'? → The right to express opinions without government punishment' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,423 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 3. What happened to the Cleveland Browns name and colors when the team moved? → They stayed in Cleveland for a future team' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,423 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 4. What is a 'guerrilla' in this historical context? → A person who fights against a government' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,423 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 5. Why is it important to regularly inspect dams? → To prevent potential failures that could cause flooding and loss of life' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,424 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 6. What makes "Meet the Press" special in television history? → It's the longest-running television program in history' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,424 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 7. How did Theodore Roosevelt unexpectedly become president? → President McKinley died and Roosevelt was Vice President' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,425 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 8. How was this first football game different from modern football? → Each team had 25 players instead of 11' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,425 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 9. Why was Abraham Lincoln able to become president with only 40% of the popular vote? → The election was split between four candidates instead of two' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,426 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 10. How old was King Henry III when the Charter of the Forest was sealed? → 10 years old' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,426 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 11. What was Pope John XII accused of doing? → Leading an armed rebellion against Emperor Otto I' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,427 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 12. How many towers of Constantinople's walls were destroyed in the earthquake? → 57 towers' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,427 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 13. What important lesson can we learn from Aaron Hernandez's story? → That making good choices is more important than being famous' (page 33)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,428 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 14. What special achievement makes Colson Whitehead stand out among authors? → He won the Pulitzer Prize twice' (page 33)
