2025-05-27 02:53:18,858 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 1. Before becoming a U.S. Senator, what position did Tammy Baldwin hold? → Member of the House of Representatives' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,858 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 2. What is 'freedom of speech'? → The right to express opinions without government punishment' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,859 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 3. What happened to the Cleveland Browns name and colors when the team moved? → They stayed in Cleveland for a future team' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,859 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 4. What is a 'guerrilla' in this historical context? → A person who fights against a government' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,860 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 5. Why is it important to regularly inspect dams? → To prevent potential failures that could cause flooding and loss of life' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,860 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 6. What makes "Meet the Press" special in television history? → It's the longest-running television program in history' (page 34)
