2025-05-27 02:53:18,861 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 9. Why was Abraham Lincoln able to become president with only 40% of the popular vote? → The election was split between four candidates instead of two' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,862 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 10. How old was King Henry III when the Charter of the Forest was sealed? → 10 years old' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,862 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 11. What was Pope John XII accused of doing? → Leading an armed rebellion against Emperor Otto I' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,863 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 12. How many towers of Constantinople's walls were destroyed in the earthquake? → 57 towers' (page 34)
2025-05-27 02:53:18,863 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='• 13. What important lesson can we learn from Aaron Hernandez's story? → That making good choices is more important than being famous' (page 34)
