2025-05-27 02:53:25,389 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='From Frozen Ponds to Hockey Stardom!' (page 37)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,390 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1995, Sam Reinhart grew up in a true Canadian hockey family with two brothers who also became NHL players! As a kid, Sam was so talented that he was picked SECOND overall in the NHL draft when he was just a teenager. That's like being the second-best kid at something in the ENTIRE WORLD! He started his career with the Buffalo Sabres and later became a star with the Florida Panthers, scoring goals and making plays that left fans jumping out of their seats. In 2023, Sam helped his team reach the Stanley Cup Finals—the biggest stage in hockey—proving that years of practicing on frozen Canadian ponds can lead to incredible achievements!' (page 37)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,391 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='Rugby Warrior from Down Under!' (page 37)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,391 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1994 in Australia, Isaah Yeo grew up to become one of rugby league's most respected players! As a kid from the countryside town of Dubbo, Isaah worked incredibly hard to make it to the big leagues. Now he's the co-captain of the Penrith Panthers team that won THREE championships in a row—an amazing feat in such a tough sport! Rugby league is like football but with no helmets or pads, just pure toughness and skill. Standing at 6'3" and weighing over 230 pounds, Isaah crashes into other players with the force of a truck but has the hands of a magician when passing the ball. His leadership and never-give-up attitude have made him a hero to young sports fans across Australia!' (page 37)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,392 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='Volleyball Queen of the Sky!' (page 37)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,392 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1992 in Bulgaria (a country in Eastern Europe), Nasya Dimitrova grew up to become a volleyball superstar with an incredible jumping ability! In volleyball, players need to leap high above the net to spike the ball down on their opponents, and Nasya could soar like she had invisible wings! As she grew up, her powerful serves and spikes helped her join professional teams and represent Bulgaria in international competitions. Volleyball is HUGE in Bulgaria—it's one of the country's favorite sports! Standing at 6'0" tall with arms that could stretch for days, Nasya became known for her amazing athleticism and competitive spirit. Her journey shows that with dedication and practice, you can rise above challenges (literally!) and represent your country on the world stage!' (page 37)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,439 - INFO - ✅ Page 38: Applied background image successfully
2025-05-27 02:53:25,440 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Supermarket Striker' (page 38)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,440 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='That's the incredible journey of Conor Sammon! Born in 1986 in Dublin, Ireland, Conor wasn't always a professional athlete. In fact, he worked a regular job at a supermarket while playing for a small local team. But Conor had big dreams and amazing determination! His talent for scoring goals got noticed, and at age 21, he made the huge leap from stacking groceries to professional soccer. Conor went on to play for major teams in Scotland and England, even competing in the English Premier League—one of the world's top soccer leagues! His most magical moment came when he was selected to represent his country, Ireland, in international matches. From supermarket aisles to packed stadiums, Conor's story shows that it's never too late to chase your dreams!' (page 38)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,441 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='From Rookie to All-Star: The Ricky Romero Story' (page 38)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,442 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='When the Toronto Blue Jays selected Ricky Romero as their first-round draft pick in 2005, many fans actually booed! They thought the team had made a mistake. But Ricky, whose parents had immigrated from Mexico to California, was determined to prove everyone wrong. And boy, did he ever! By 2011, this left-handed pitching wizard had transformed into an All-Star player, silencing all those doubters. Ricky's devastating changeup pitch baffled batters, and his incredible work ethic inspired teammates. Though injuries eventually challenged his career, Ricky's journey from draft day disappointment to baseball stardom shows that sometimes the people who don't believe in you are the best motivation to succeed!' (page 38)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,442 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='From Rookie to Rebound Master!' (page 38)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,443 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1981, Luke Jackson soared through the basketball world like a superhero! This high-flying forward from the University of Oregon was so incredible at jumping and dunking that fans would gasp whenever he took flight. In 2004, he was chosen as the 10th pick in the NBA draft by the Cleveland Cavaliers and got to play alongside the legendary LeBron James! Though injuries tried to ground this Skywalker, Luke never gave up. After his playing days, he took all his basketball wisdom and became a coach, teaching the next generation how to reach for the stars—literally and figuratively!' (page 38)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,489 - INFO - ✅ Page 39: Applied background image successfully
2025-05-27 02:53:25,490 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Baseball Star Who Walked Away!' (page 39)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,491 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Adam LaRoche, born in 1979, wasn't just any baseball player—he was a slugging first baseman who could smack home runs like he was swatting flies! After playing 12 amazing seasons in Major League Baseball for teams like the Atlanta Braves and Washington Nationals, Adam did something that shocked the sports world. In 2016, he walked away from a $13 MILLION contract (that's enough money to buy about 2.6 million baseball gloves!) because his team wouldn't let his son spend time with him in the clubhouse. Adam believed family came first—even before fame and fortune! Today, he runs a ranch and fights against human trafficking, showing that sometimes the biggest home runs in life happen off the baseball field.' (page 39)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,492 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Basketball Champion Who Beat the Odds!' (page 39)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,492 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1979, Lamar Odom's life story reads like an action-packed movie! Growing up in a tough neighborhood in Queens, New York, Lamar lost his mom when he was just 12 years old—but he channeled his grief into basketball. His incredible skills (he was 6'10" tall but could handle the ball like someone much smaller!) took him all the way to the NBA, where he became famous for doing a little bit of everything on the court. Lamar won TWO championships with the Los Angeles Lakers and even earned the NBA's Sixth Man of the Year award in 2011! Though he faced personal struggles later in life, including a scary medical emergency in 2015, Lamar showed amazing courage by fighting back and sharing his story to help others.' (page 39)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,493 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Hockey Hurricane from Carolina!' (page 39)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,493 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1978, Erik Cole zoomed from small-town New York onto the biggest hockey stages in the world! This lightning-fast left winger became famous for his incredible speed, helping the Carolina Hurricanes win their first-ever Stanley Cup championship in 2006. But Erik's journey wasn't always smooth skating—after suffering a broken neck from a dangerous hit, doctors weren't sure if he'd ever play again. But through determination and courage, Erik made an amazing comeback to the ice, showing kids everywhere that with enough heart, you can overcome even the biggest obstacles!' (page 39)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,539 - INFO - ✅ Page 40: Applied background image successfully
2025-05-27 02:53:25,541 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Football Star Who Became a Hero' (page 40)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,541 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Pat Tillman wasn't just any football player—he was an NFL star for the Arizona Cardinals who shocked the world in 2002 when he turned down a $3.6 million contract to join the U.S. Army after the September 11 attacks. Born in 1976, Pat believed that some things were more important than fame or money. He became an Army Ranger, one of the toughest soldiers in the military! Sadly, Pat lost his life while serving in Afghanistan in 2004. His incredible sacrifice inspired people across America to think about what true courage means. Today, the Pat Tillman Foundation helps military veterans and their spouses go to college, continuing his legacy of service and dedication to others.' (page 40)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,542 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Color Wizard of Comic Books' (page 40)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,542 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1966, Stephanie Vozzo became one of the unsung heroes of the comic book world! As a professional colorist, she used her amazing artistic skills to bring comic book characters to life with vibrant colors. Before computers took over, colorists like Stephanie had to hand-paint color guides for printers, making precise decisions about every shade and hue. Her work has appeared in countless comic books that kids and adults have enjoyed for decades. But Stephanie didn't stop there! She also became a music agent, helping musicians find places to perform and building their careers. Talk about having colorful talents in completely different fields!' (page 40)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,543 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Almost Space Explorer' (page 40)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,544 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Nadezhda Kuzhelnaya was born in 1962 and grew up to become one of Russia's most skilled pilots. But that wasn't enough for her - she wanted the stars! After years of tough training, she was selected to be a cosmonaut (that's what Russians call their astronauts). She prepared for missions to the International Space Station and even trained as a backup crew member, ready to blast off if needed. Though she never actually flew a mission to space, Nadezhda broke barriers as one of the few women in Russia's space program. Her determination showed kids everywhere that sometimes just chasing your biggest dreams is an adventure all by itself!' (page 40)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,590 - INFO - ✅ Page 41: Applied background image successfully
2025-05-27 02:53:25,591 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Kennedy Cousin Who Became a News Star' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,592 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1955, Maria Shriver didn't just rely on her famous Kennedy family name (she's the niece of President John F. Kennedy!). Instead, she charged into the world of journalism, becoming a respected TV news anchor and award-winning reporter. She interviewed world leaders, covered major events, and wrote books that inspired millions. While she was once California's First Lady when married to actor-turned-governor Arnold Schwarzenegger, Maria's biggest impact has been through her journalism and advocacy work for Alzheimer's research and women's empowerment. She proved that even when you come from a super-famous family, your own voice and hard work can make the biggest difference!' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,592 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Cricket Captain Who Flew Planes!' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,593 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Geoff Rabone was no ordinary cricket player! Born in New Zealand in 1921, Geoff became famous for his skills with both bat and ball. But what makes his story EXTRA amazing is that during World War II, he was a brave pilot who flew 40 dangerous bombing missions! Can you imagine going from dodging enemy fire to hitting cricket balls? After the war, Geoff became the captain of New Zealand's national cricket team and led them on their first-ever tour of South Africa. He was known for being super smart about cricket strategy and for never giving up, even when his team was losing. Geoff showed that the same courage that makes someone a war hero can also make them a sports champion!' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,593 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Ufton Nervet Railway Mystery' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,594 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='On a dark November evening in 2004, a high-speed train with hundreds of passengers was zooming through the English countryside near a small village called Ufton Nervet. Without warning, the train crashed into a car that had stopped on the railway crossing. The massive train, weighing as heavy as 50 elephants, derailed—sending carriages tumbling off the tracks. While most passengers survived, seven people lost their lives and 150 were injured. The accident led to important changes in railway safety, with engineers developing new ways to make crossings safer and train cars stronger. Sometimes it takes a tragedy to help us learn how to protect people better in the future.' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,595 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Teacher Who Led a Nation' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,595 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Nimalan Soundaranayagam began his journey as a dedicated teacher in Sri Lanka, a beautiful island nation in the Indian Ocean. But he didn't stop at just helping students learn—he believed he could help his whole country! Nimalan became both an important educator AND a politician, working to improve schools while also representing his people in government. Sadly, during a time when Sri Lanka faced serious conflicts, Nimalan's life was cut short in 2000. His courage to be both a teacher and a leader showed that sometimes the people who teach us can also help guide our nations.' (page 41)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,641 - INFO - ✅ Page 42: Applied background image successfully
2025-05-27 02:53:25,643 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactTitle, text='The Goalkeeper with Golden Gloves' (page 42)
2025-05-27 02:53:25,644 - INFO - 🧩 afterFlowable: style=FactStory, text='Born in 1992 in Germany, Stefan Ortega grew up to become an incredible soccer goalkeeper with lightning-fast reflexes and nerves of steel. As a kid playing in local German fields, Stefan probably never imagined he'd one day be blocking shots from some of the world's greatest strikers! His journey took him through German clubs like Arminia Bielefeld before reaching the English Premier League with Manchester City, one of the world's top teams. Standing between the goalposts, Stefan has made spectacular diving saves that seem to defy gravity, showing that sometimes the most important player on the field isn't the one scoring goals—it's the one preventing them!' (page 42)
